                            <comment id="14415417" author="ID134349" created="Sun, 4 Oct 2009 19:23:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am curious why, if it was working in 2.0.x, it only is fixed in 3.0? I think this counts as a regression for 2.2.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14415360" author="marc.rohlfs" created="Mon, 5 Oct 2009 03:18:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Paul, I think You&apos;re right. This issue should have been marked as a regression. Do You think we might reopen it to get it fixed in 2.2.2? I&apos;d really like to use some of the new features that were introduced in Maven 2.2, but this issue prevents me from upgrading.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14415467" author="marc.rohlfs" created="Wed, 28 Oct 2009 17:45:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for Maven-2.2.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14415326" author="marc.rohlfs" created="Wed, 28 Oct 2009 17:59:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Benjamin,&lt;br/&gt;
I provided a patch to fix this issue on the branch &lt;tt&gt;maven-2.2.x&lt;/tt&gt;. Could You please add this fix to the release 2.2.2?&lt;br/&gt;
Many thanks!!!&lt;br/&gt;
Kind regards&lt;br/&gt;
Marc&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14415500" author="marc.rohlfs" created="Thu, 29 Oct 2009 18:29:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Those files provide a patch to extend the integration test for this issue. As I renamed (and moved) some files - which isn&apos;t properly covered by the SVN patch -, I provided a script to prepare the SVN changes in addition to the patch. Execute the script first and then apply the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14415392" author="marc.rohlfs" created="Thu, 29 Oct 2009 18:43:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When I created the patch for this issue, I noticed that the &lt;tt&gt;phase&lt;/tt&gt; interpolation wouldn&apos;t work either (and fixed it, too).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore I extended the integration test for this issue. As I renamed (and moved) some files - which isn&apos;t properly covered by the SVN patch -, I provided both, a script to prepare the SVN changes and the patch for the extended integration test itself. Execute the script first and then apply the patch - if You consider to accept the patch(es).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
